Rating: 4
So, like other reviewers, I used this as a base recipe and expanded from there. I left the skins on the potatoes (they were tiny, it was easier that way), and I sautéed some onions, garlic and red pepper flakes. I had a wee bit of cream in the fridge that I needed to use up, so I added that and the pesto. It was fantastic! And there's a ton, so I have lunch for at least two days!

